      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "In /Users/jaronswab/go/src/github.com/jrswab/axe, run:\n1. `go build ./...`\n2. `go test ./internal/hostcheck/`\n3. `go test ./internal/agent/`\n4. `go test ./internal/tool/`\n5. `go test ./cmd/`\n6. `golangci-lint run ./...`\n7. `git diff --shortstat`\n\nThen commit:\n```bash\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"fix: harden allowlist implementation (ISS-24)\n\n- Add nil resolver guard and wrap DNS errors with hostname context\n- Distinguish nil vs empty AllowedHosts for sub-agent inheritance\n  (nil = inherit parent, empty = explicit opt-out)\n- Move timeout context before host check to bound DNS I/O\n- DialContext re-resolves per redirect to prevent stale IP pinning\n- Restore allowlist check in CheckRedirect for keep-alive safety\n- Add allowed_hosts to scaffold template\n- Update spec E5 for nil-vs-empty semantics\"\n```\n\nThen push:\n```bash\ngit push\n```\n\nReturn all output.",
